What is Multithreading? What is the difference between a thread and a process?

Multithreading is the ability of a central processing unit (CPU) (or a single core in a multi-core processor) 
to provide multiple threads of execution concurrently, supported by the operating system.


Difference between Thread and Process

A thread is a lightweight sub-process, the smallest unit of processing. Multiprocessing and multithreading, both are used to achieve multitasking.

A Process is a single program that runs to do some functionality


Multiple threads are there inside of a process 




